**At Bayer we’re visionaries, driven to solve the world’s toughest challenges and striving for a world where 'Health for all Hunger for none’ is no longer a dream, but a real possibility. We’re doing it with energy, curiosity and sheer dedication, always learning from unique perspectives of those around us, expanding our thinking, growing our capabilities and redefining ‘impossible’. There are so many reasons to join us. If you’re hungry to build a varied and meaningful career in a community of brilliant and diverse minds to make a real difference, there’s only one choice.**




**Sales Analyst Intern**




**YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES**




The primary responsibilities of this role are to:


* Work with a cross functional teams to develop national and/or brand category plans and strategies for the assigned project, which align Sales Strategy and Operations and Marketing objectives to customer needs;
* Assist in pulling and analyzing syndicated and customer POS data;
* Develop recommendations based on the analysis of data from various sources;
* Assist the team to enhance and improve business results;
* Communicate results, ideas and/or suggestions both in written and verbal format;
* Interact with Bayer Consumer Health (BCH) colleagues in a variety of job functions within Consumer Health Sales Strategy & Operations, Marketing, and Customer Teams/Field Sales;
* Develop negotiation tactics to deliver mutually acceptable outputs;
* Upon completion of Internship, candidate will conduct an oral presentation of project results and key learnings to Bayer management.






**WHO YOU ARE**




Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:




Required Qualifications:


* Must be pursuing a four year degree in a Business field;
* Available May 2024 to August 2024;
* You must be willing to commit to the entire 12 weeks, 40 hours per week, Monday Friday;
* Must be eligible to work in the US now and in the future;
* Candidate must be able to demonstrate work experience or capability in the following areas:
	+ Solid written and verbal communication skills that allow for clear and concise presentations;
	+ Highly organized with strong attention to detail;
	+ Results oriented with the ability to manage and prioritize multiple projects and deliverables effectively;
* Proven problem solving skills;
* Ability to demonstrate initiative, self direction, and collaboration capabilities;
* Be proficient in Windows software applications (Excel, PowerPoint, Word, Outlook);
* Able to provide own transportation to and from work office location in Whippany, NJ.
* Ability to travel as needed for in person meetings or training;
* Able to demonstrate work experience and/or capability in the following areas: Leadership, Analytics, Collaboration, Communication, Project management, Self direction and initiative.






Preferred Qualifications


* Preferably a Junior pursuing completion of their undergraduate business or marketing degree;
* Candidates interested in Sales or Marketing are preferred.
* Experience with IRI or Nielson POS data preferred;
* Cumulative GPA 3.3 or higher, is highly preferred or demonstrated leadership and initiative;




**YOUR APPLICATION**  





Bayer offers a wide variety of competitive compensation and benefits programs. If you meet the requirements of this unique opportunity, and want to impact our mission Science for a better life, we encourage you to apply now. Be part of something bigger. Be you. Be Bayer.  

To all recruitment agencies: Bayer does not accept unsolicited third party resumes.  



